Define the documentation structure and migration sequence for a single Doxygen Awesome-driven site, so each step creates reusable final assets rather than throwaway approximations. The resulting site must keep the familiar libcwd entry points while using Doxygen-generated Markdown pages, Doxygen layout/navigation/search where applicable, vendored Doxygen Awesome assets, and predictable cross-links between About libcwd, release notes, tutorial, reference manual, quick reference, repository, and downloads.
